# Cartwheel Arts — Cursor Rules

## Project

This is a kids art class registration web app for Cartwheel Arts (cartwheelarts.org).

Stack: React + Vite, Firestore (Firebase), Firebase Auth, Firebase Cloud Functions, Stripe (payments), Resend (email), Firebase Storage, deployed to Vercel.

## Code Style

- Use functional React components with hooks only (no class components)
- Use async/await, never raw `.then()` chains
- Always add error handling with try/catch on async operations
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (or `src/theme.js` tokens for brand colors/fonts)
- Keep components small and single-purpose
- Name files with PascalCase for components, camelCase for utilities

## Firebase

- Never expose Firebase admin credentials in client-side code
- Use Firestore security rules — never bypass them
- All writes that affect `spotsRemaining` must use Firestore transactions

## Stripe

- Always use Stripe Checkout (hosted) — never build a custom card form
- Payment confirmation must come from a webhook, never from client-side redirect alone

## General

- The primary user of this app is a non-technical small business owner
- Prefer clarity and simplicity over clever code
- Always explain what a generated file does in a brief comment at the top
